I have played this game for years. It became unplayable after the recent Android update as many others have said. I managed to find a way to fix the issue! With the game open, click the "Game Booster" icon in the bottom left corner and then click on the gear icon in the top right of the Game Booster UI. Once there, click "Full screen apps". Make the app is set to auto and then click the ellipsis in the top right and click advanced settings. Turn on "Hide Camera Cutout" Enjoy!
Still playing after all these years. Thanks! ~john

This is probably one of the best Billiards games that you'll find on the Play Store. Not only does it have online multiplayer, but it also has options for offline play as well, including the computer's skill level.   One of my favorite mechanics is the prediction lines, which you can toggle on or off as you prefer. Really useful as practice for when I play pool in real life. It's also great as a quick game if I'm bored or waiting somewhere.   The only downside I can think of is the dated menu and button design. It's basically Gingerbread-era Android buttons. Functional, but not so pretty to look at. Still, not a big enough problem to dissuade me from playing this daily. Keep up the good work, devs!

I was a big fan of the Virtual Pool PC games in the 90s. This game is very similar and I bought the Pro version right away. However the muliplayer experience is ruined by a few problems:  1) There is no consequence for people who abandon games. 2) There is a very easy way to cheat on games with short guides for object balls and the free camera view which makes it easy for anyone to make  difficult shots and run 15 reds in snooker. 3) There is no way to refuse games where a player wants to use guide lines (cheat lines). You can request a game without guides but the game will automatically pair you with games that have guides and you have no choice. I'll be checking out other similar games to see if their multiplayer is better.

You can adjust many physical aspects of the way the ball travels -- but you don't need to. Just grab your cue and shoot. If you're not good at pool or geometry, don't worry. The game helps you shoot straight or with English and shows you where the ball is headed. And the levels of diffculty and oponents can challenge  any players skill level. Oh, and there NO in-game purchases -- try the "Lite" version and you will want to throw in your buck and play without ads and play network  players.  Edit: I have to add that the game docmentation (Help, How to play) goes into great detail and is written in plain English. It, along with the game itself, is done so professionally. I imagine that if a person were able to puchase a PC or Game Console version, it should cost from $49.90 to $69.99.  Also, the graphics, rendering and speed are remarkable on my Note 10.1 but if you have problems on a phone, there are several GPU settings that can be tuned and optimized for any device.
replyContent: Thanks for such a detailed review.

replyContent: There is NO Admob in the paid version. Not sure what your detector is checking for but the admob SDK (library) that serves ads is absent from the paid version. That is the difference in the apk file size between the pro and the lite versions. And because the library is absent, all admob related code is absent as well - otherwise the app would crash

This is simply the best snooker game I've ever played - better even than games on my PC. You've got endless varieties of snooker and pool to choose from - including both British and American, along with 'Carrom' and 'Crokinole': two very unique and playable cue-based games that use something like pucks rather than balls. You've got a first person perspective, a realistic AI, and it just feels so much like the real thing (ie pool is just as easy and snooker just as hard as in a real club). Worth every penny!

I recently started playing pool again in June of this year, and much to my dismay there were no decent pool apps on android or iOS. This is beyond the scope of what I imagined a portable pool game could be. Everything from English to vertical cue angle can be adjusted. The online functionality and awesome ai really bring the package together. This is the best pool game I have ever played on any platform and I say that with no exaggeration. And for only 99 cents? Sweet! Well earned five stars dev!
